{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01DshDtT9WDTGPZuuhDNzvTz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive picture of all the relevant YAML examples. Let me compile the findings.\n\n---\n\nHere is a complete report of the MachineConfig YAML examples found across the repo, organized by the three features you asked about.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Adding files via `spec.config.storage.files`\n\n### docs/MachineConfig.md (Ignition v3.2, current/recommended)\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: worker-2864988432\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.2.0\n    storage:\n      files:\n      - contents:\n          source: data:,%20\n        mode: 384\n        path: /root/myfile\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md` (lines 62-77)\n\n### docs/MachineConfig.md (Ignition v2.2, clusters < 4.6)\n\nThe older form requires a `filesystem: root` field on each file entry:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 2.2.0\n    storage:\n      files:\n      - contents:\n          source: data:,%20\n        filesystem: root\n        mode: 384\n        path: /root/myfile\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md` (lines 79-97)\n\n### pkg/server/testdata/machine-configs/test-config.yaml (complete real-world example)\n\nThis is the most detailed YAML file in the repo. It combines `kernelArguments`, `storage.files`, and `systemd.units` in one object:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: test-config\nspec:\n  osImageURL: registry.example.com/oscontainer@sha256:b5bb9d8014a0f9b1d61e21e796d78dccdf1352f23cd32812f4850b878ae4944c\n  kernelArguments:\n    - foo=bar\n    - nosmt\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: \"2.2.0\"\n    storage:\n      files:\n        -\n          contents:\n            source: \"data:,GROUP%3Dstable%0ASERVER%3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A32003%2Fv1%2Fupdate%0A\"\n            verification: {}\n          filesystem: root\n          mode: 420\n          path: /etc/coreos/update.conf\n    systemd:\n      units:\n        - ...\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/server/testdata/machine-configs/test-config.yaml`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Setting `kernelArguments`\n\n### docs/MachineConfig.md — targeting master nodes\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: \"master\"\n  name: 99-master-kargs-loglevel\nspec:\n  kernelArguments:\n    - 'loglevel=7'\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md` (lines 122-132)\n\n### docs/MachineConfig.md — targeting worker nodes (from \"Known Issue\" section)\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: worker\n  name: worker-kargs\nspec:\n  kernelArguments:\n    - foo\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md` (lines 147-157)\n\n### test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-worker-kernel-selinux.yaml\n\nOpenShift Template wrapping a MachineConfig; the pool is parameterized but the structure is real:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.2.0\n  kernelArguments:\n    - enforcing=0\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-worker-kernel-selinux.yaml`\n\n### test/extended-priv/testdata/files/add-ignition-kernel-arguments.yaml\n\nShows the newer Ignition v3.4 `kernelArguments` placement inside `spec.config` (not at the top-level `spec`):\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.4.0\n    kernelArguments:\n      shouldExist:\n      - enforcing=0\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/add-ignition-kernel-arguments.yaml`\n\nNote: This is the Ignition-native `kernelArguments` field (inside `spec.config`), distinct from the MCO-native `spec.kernelArguments` (at the top level of `spec`). Both forms exist in the repo.\n\n### test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-worker-karg-ktype-extension.yaml\n\nShows `kernelArguments` combined with `kernelType` and `extensions`:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.2.0\n  extensions:\n    - usbguard\n  kernelType: realtime\n  kernelArguments:\n    - 'z=10'\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-worker-karg-ktype-extension.yaml`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Targeting worker nodes (`role: worker`)\n\nThe label used is `machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: worker`.\n\n### docs/MachineConfig.md — RT kernel on workers\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: \"worker\"\n  name: worker-kerneltype\nspec:\n  kernelType: realtime\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md` (lines 192-200)\n\n### docs/MachineConfig.md — usbguard extension on workers\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: worker\n  name: worker-extensions\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.2.0\n  extensions:\n    - usbguard\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md` (lines 218-231)\n\n### docs/Update-SSHKeys.md — SSH keys on workers\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: worker\n  name: 99-worker-ssh\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 2.2.0\n    passwd:\n      users:\n      - name: core\n        sshAuthorizedKeys:\n        - ssh-rsa ABC123....\n        - ssh-ed25519 XYZ7890....\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/Update-SSHKeys.md` (lines 31-48)\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Patterns\n\n| Feature | Where set | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `spec.config.storage.files` | Inside the Ignition config blob at `spec.config` | `source` uses data URIs (RFC 2397); `mode` is octal as decimal (e.g., 420 = 0644, 384 = 0600); `filesystem: root` only required for Ignition v2.x |\n| `spec.kernelArguments` | Top-level `spec` field (MCO-native) | Plain list of strings; triggers a node reboot |\n| `machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: worker` | `metadata.labels` | Selects the `worker` MachineConfigPool; use `master` for control-plane nodes |\n\nThe most complete single-file YAML example combining `kernelArguments` + `storage.files` together is at `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/server/testdata/machine-configs/test-config.yaml`. The canonical documentation examples live in `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md`. The test template fixtures under `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/` are parameterized OpenShift Templates but show real `kernelArguments` structures for current Ignition versions (3.2–3.4)."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b3810a3c-eea7-4cd5-9b89-22b4f26138cd","uuid":"9fa4e89b-623c-4b7b-84db-f953e416b0b8","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:11:57.950Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search for MachineConfig YAML examples in the machine-config-operator repo at /home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator that show:\n1. Adding files via the spec.config.storage.files field\n2. Setting kernelArguments\n3. Targeting worker nodes (role: worker)\n\nLook in: docs/, examples/, test/e2e/, and any *.yaml or *.md files. Find real YAML examples showing the complete MachineConfig structure. Search breadth: medium.","agentId":"a472ace94b5ff04dd","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive picture of all the relevant YAML examples. Let me compile the findings.\n\n---\n\nHere is a complete report of the MachineConfig YAML examples found across the repo, organized by the three features you asked about.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Adding files via `spec.config.storage.files`\n\n### docs/MachineConfig.md (Ignition v3.2, current/recommended)\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: worker-2864988432\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.2.0\n    storage:\n      files:\n      - contents:\n          source: data:,%20\n        mode: 384\n        path: /root/myfile\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md` (lines 62-77)\n\n### docs/MachineConfig.md (Ignition v2.2, clusters < 4.6)\n\nThe older form requires a `filesystem: root` field on each file entry:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 2.2.0\n    storage:\n      files:\n      - contents:\n          source: data:,%20\n        filesystem: root\n        mode: 384\n        path: /root/myfile\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md` (lines 79-97)\n\n### pkg/server/testdata/machine-configs/test-config.yaml (complete real-world example)\n\nThis is the most detailed YAML file in the repo. It combines `kernelArguments`, `storage.files`, and `systemd.units` in one object:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: test-config\nspec:\n  osImageURL: registry.example.com/oscontainer@sha256:b5bb9d8014a0f9b1d61e21e796d78dccdf1352f23cd32812f4850b878ae4944c\n  kernelArguments:\n    - foo=bar\n    - nosmt\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: \"2.2.0\"\n    storage:\n      files:\n        -\n          contents:\n            source: \"data:,GROUP%3Dstable%0ASERVER%3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A32003%2Fv1%2Fupdate%0A\"\n            verification: {}\n          filesystem: root\n          mode: 420\n          path: /etc/coreos/update.conf\n    systemd:\n      units:\n        - ...\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/server/testdata/machine-configs/test-config.yaml`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Setting `kernelArguments`\n\n### docs/MachineConfig.md — targeting master nodes\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: \"master\"\n  name: 99-master-kargs-loglevel\nspec:\n  kernelArguments:\n    - 'loglevel=7'\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md` (lines 122-132)\n\n### docs/MachineConfig.md — targeting worker nodes (from \"Known Issue\" section)\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: worker\n  name: worker-kargs\nspec:\n  kernelArguments:\n    - foo\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md` (lines 147-157)\n\n### test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-worker-kernel-selinux.yaml\n\nOpenShift Template wrapping a MachineConfig; the pool is parameterized but the structure is real:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.2.0\n  kernelArguments:\n    - enforcing=0\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-worker-kernel-selinux.yaml`\n\n### test/extended-priv/testdata/files/add-ignition-kernel-arguments.yaml\n\nShows the newer Ignition v3.4 `kernelArguments` placement inside `spec.config` (not at the top-level `spec`):\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.4.0\n    kernelArguments:\n      shouldExist:\n      - enforcing=0\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/add-ignition-kernel-arguments.yaml`\n\nNote: This is the Ignition-native `kernelArguments` field (inside `spec.config`), distinct from the MCO-native `spec.kernelArguments` (at the top level of `spec`). Both forms exist in the repo.\n\n### test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-worker-karg-ktype-extension.yaml\n\nShows `kernelArguments` combined with `kernelType` and `extensions`:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.2.0\n  extensions:\n    - usbguard\n  kernelType: realtime\n  kernelArguments:\n    - 'z=10'\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-worker-karg-ktype-extension.yaml`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Targeting worker nodes (`role: worker`)\n\nThe label used is `machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: worker`.\n\n### docs/MachineConfig.md — RT kernel on workers\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: \"worker\"\n  name: worker-kerneltype\nspec:\n  kernelType: realtime\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md` (lines 192-200)\n\n### docs/MachineConfig.md — usbguard extension on workers\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: worker\n  name: worker-extensions\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.2.0\n  extensions:\n    - usbguard\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md` (lines 218-231)\n\n### docs/Update-SSHKeys.md — SSH keys on workers\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: worker\n  name: 99-worker-ssh\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 2.2.0\n    passwd:\n      users:\n      - name: core\n        sshAuthorizedKeys:\n        - ssh-rsa ABC123....\n        - ssh-ed25519 XYZ7890....\n```\n\nFile: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/Update-SSHKeys.md` (lines 31-48)\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Patterns\n\n| Feature | Where set | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `spec.config.storage.files` | Inside the Ignition config blob at `spec.config` | `source` uses data URIs (RFC 2397); `mode` is octal as decimal (e.g., 420 = 0644, 384 = 0600); `filesystem: root` only required for Ignition v2.x |\n| `spec.kernelArguments` | Top-level `spec` field (MCO-native) | Plain list of strings; triggers a node reboot |\n| `machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: worker` | `metadata.labels` | Selects the `worker` MachineConfigPool; use `master` for control-plane nodes |\n\nThe most complete single-file YAML example combining `kernelArguments` + `storage.files` together is at `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/server/testdata/machine-configs/test-config.yaml`. The canonical documentation examples live in `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md`. The test template fixtures under `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/` are parameterized OpenShift Templates but show real `kernelArguments` structures for current Ignition versions (3.2–3.4)."}],"resolvedModel":"claude-sonnet-4-6","totalDurationMs":117603,"totalTokens":53382,"totalToolUseCount":41,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":548,"cache_read_input_tokens":50404,"outp